Wynnewood coordinates its emergency response program and response actions with the Garvin County Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC). This coordination includes quarterly meetings of the committee, which includes local emergency response officials, local government officials, and industry representatives. In addition to quarterly LEPC meetings, the refnery participates in emergency drills conducted by the LEPC that involve area emergency responders. The refinery has 24/7 communication capability with appropriate LEPC officials and emergency response organizations to provide a means of notifying the public of an incident as well as facilitating quick response to an incident.



6 PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY



Wynnewood is continuously investigating and reviewing technology and/or applications that could possibly enhance its safety efforts. These currently include:



- Fire Water System evaluation;

- Additional Deluge fire protection;

- Emergency Isolation Valves evaluation;

- Dual Seals on Pumps;

- Expanded emergency drills for HF;

- Personnel accounability system evaluation; and,

- Additional safety showers.
